
RootApplicationContext and WebApplicationContext.
	 A web application can define any number of DispatcherServlets.
	 Each servlet will operate in its own namespace, loading its own application context with mappings, handlers, etc.
 	 Only the root application context as loaded by {@link org.springframework.web.context.ContextLoaderListener}, if any, will be shared.


	request -> HandlerMapping Object -> Handler adapter Object -> InternalResourceViewResolver

	
	DefaultRequestToViewNameTranslator
	



Spring frameworkd internally make use of DocumentBuillderFactory to parse xml document.
